<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="590" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,691,1149]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis box="[151,257,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">Remarks.</emphasis>
For a long time, the oplophorid shrimps were considered to consist of a single pelagic family, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[1282,1436,691,717]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Oplophoridae</taxonomicName>
s.l., including 10 genera and about 70 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Chace, F. A. Jr." box="[688,835,727,754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 82" refId="ref5019" refString="Chace, F. A. Jr. (1986) The caridean shrimps (Crustacea: Decapoda) of the Albratross Philippine Expedition, 1907 - 1910, Part 4: Oplophoridae and Nematocarcinidae. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 432, 1 - 82. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.432" type="journal article" year="1986">Chace, 1986</bibRefCitation>
). Recently, the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[1012,1166,727,753]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Oplophoridae</taxonomicName>
has been the subject of several molecular studies seeking to better understand the phylogeny of the family. Bracken-Grissom, 
<emphasis box="[1299,1347,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">et.al</emphasis>
. (2009) found very little support for a monophyletic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[660,814,799,825]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Oplophoridae</taxonomicName>
and split the family into the families 
<taxonomicName authority="Spence Bate (1888)" authorityName="Spence Bate" authorityYear="1888" class="Malacostraca" family="Acanthephyridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Acanthephyridae 
<bibRefCitation author="Spence Bate, C." box="[151,383,835,861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 942" refId="ref5965" refString="Spence Bate, C. (1888) Report on the Crustacea Macrura collected by the Challenger during the years 1873 - 76. Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of H. M. S. &quot; Challenger &quot; during the years 1873 - 76, 24, 1 - 942." type="journal article" year="1888">Spence Bate (1888)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, containing seven genera: 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Milne-Edwards, 1881" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1881" box="[699,1155,835,861]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Acanthephyra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[699,856,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">Acanthephyra</emphasis>
A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Milne-Edwards, A." box="[905,1155,835,861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref5480" refString="Milne-Edwards, A. (1881) Description de quelques crustaces macroures provenant des grandes profondeura de la mar des Antilles. Annales des Sciences Naturelles, 11, 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1881">Milne-Edwards, 1881</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith, 1885" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1885" box="[1172,1432,834,861]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Ephyrina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1172,1276,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">Ephyrina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, S. I." box="[1288,1432,834,861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="493 - 511" refId="ref5858" refString="Smith, S. I. (1885) On some new or little-known Decapod Crustacea, from recent Fish Commission dredgings off the east coast of the United States. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 7, 493 - 511. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.455.493" type="journal article" year="1885">Smith, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Chace, 1886" authorityName="Chace" authorityYear="1886" box="[151,441,871,897]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Heterogenys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,291,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">Heterogenys</emphasis>
Chace, 1886
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority=", G. O. Sars, 1877" authorityName=", G. O. Sars" authorityYear="1877" box="[451,800,871,897]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Hymenodora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[451,597,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">Hymenodora</emphasis>
, G. O. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sars, G. O." box="[679,800,871,897]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="337 - 371" refId="ref5609" refString="Sars, G. O. (1877) Prodromus descriptions Crustaceorum et Pyncogonidarum quae in Expeditione Norvegica Anno 1876 observavit. Archiv for Mathematik og Naturvidenskab, 2, 337 - 371." type="journal article" year="1877">Sars, 1877</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Chace, 1986" authorityName="Chace" authorityYear="1986" box="[810,1073,871,897]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Kemphyra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[810,927,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">Kemphyra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chace, F. A. Jr." box="[934,1073,871,897]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 82" refId="ref5019" refString="Chace, F. A. Jr. (1986) The caridean shrimps (Crustacea: Decapoda) of the Albratross Philippine Expedition, 1907 - 1910, Part 4: Oplophoridae and Nematocarcinidae. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 432, 1 - 82. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.432" type="journal article" year="1986">Chace, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith, 1882" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1882" box="[1087,1385,871,897]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Meningodora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1087,1239,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">Meningodora</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, S. I." box="[1246,1385,871,897]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 108" refId="ref5773" refString="Smith, S. I. (1882) Reports on the results of dredging under the supervision of Alexander Agassiz, on the east coast of the United States during the summer of 1880, by the U. S. Coast Survey Steamer &quot; Blake &quot;, Commander J. R. Bartlett, U. S. N., commanding. Bulletin of the Museum of comparative Zoology at Harvard College, 10 (1), 1 - 108." type="journal article" year="1882">Smith, 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Milne-Edwards, 1881" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1881" box="[151,567,907,933]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Notostomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,283,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">Notostomus</emphasis>
A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Milne-Edwards, A." box="[321,567,907,933]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref5480" refString="Milne-Edwards, A. (1881) Description de quelques crustaces macroures provenant des grandes profondeura de la mar des Antilles. Annales des Sciences Naturelles, 11, 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1881">Milne-Edwards, 1881</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; the family 
<taxonomicName authority="Dana, 1852" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[696,987,906,933]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Oplophoridae 
<bibRefCitation author="Dana, J. D." box="[856,987,906,933]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="10 - 28" refId="ref5184" refString="Dana, J. D. (1852) Conspectus Crustaceorum quae in Orbis Terrarum circumnavigatione, Carolo Wilkes e Classe Reipublicae Foederatae Duce, lexit et descripsit. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 1852, 10 - 28." type="journal article" year="1852">Dana, 1852</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was restricted to three genera: 
<taxonomicName authority="Chace, 1986" authorityName="Chace" authorityYear="1986" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Janicella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1334,1437,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">Janicella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chace, F. A. Jr." box="[151,292,943,969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 82" refId="ref5019" refString="Chace, F. A. Jr. (1986) The caridean shrimps (Crustacea: Decapoda) of the Albratross Philippine Expedition, 1907 - 1910, Part 4: Oplophoridae and Nematocarcinidae. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 432, 1 - 82. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.432" type="journal article" year="1986">Chace, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="H. Milne Edwards, 1837" authorityName="H. Milne Edwards" authorityYear="1837" box="[306,729,943,969]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Oplophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[306,440,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">Oplophorus</emphasis>
H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Milne Edwards, H." box="[483,729,943,969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 42" refId="ref5513" refString="Milne Edwards, H. (1837) Histoire naturelle des Crustaces, comprenant l'anatomie, la physilogie et la classification de ces animaux. Vol. 3. Libraire Encyclopediqu Roret, Paris, 638 pp., pls. 1 - 42." type="book chapter" year="1837">Milne Edwards, 1837</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority=", Spence Bate, 1888" authorityName=", Spence Bate" authorityYear="1888" box="[788,1147,943,969]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Systellaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[788,919,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">Systellaspis</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Spence Bate, C." box="[933,1147,943,969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="1 - 942" refId="ref5965" refString="Spence Bate, C. (1888) Report on the Crustacea Macrura collected by the Challenger during the years 1873 - 76. Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of H. M. S. &quot; Challenger &quot; during the years 1873 - 76, 24, 1 - 942." type="journal article" year="1888">Spence Bate, 1888</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. A more recent molecular study (
<bibRefCitation author="Wong, J. M. &amp; Perez-Moreno, J. L. &amp; Chan, T. Y. &amp; Frank, T. M. &amp; Branken-Grissom, H. D." box="[225,419,978,1005]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="278 - 292" refId="ref6469" refString="Wong, J. M., Perez-Moreno, J. L., Chan, T. Y., Frank, T. M. &amp; Branken-Grissom, H. D. (2015) Phylogenetic and transcriptomic analyses reveal the Evolution of bioluminescence and light detection in marine, deep-sea shrimps of the family Oplophoridae (Crustacea: Decapoda). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 83, 278 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2014.11.013" type="journal article" year="2015">
Wong 
<emphasis box="[300,348,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
) restored the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[569,723,979,1005]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Oplophoridae</taxonomicName>
to monophyly. Further, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lunina, A. A. &amp; Kulagin, D. N. &amp; Vereshchaka, A. L." box="[991,1213,979,1005]" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="213 - 232" refId="ref5406" refString="Lunina, A. A., Kulagin, D. N. &amp; Vereshchaka, A. L. (2019) Oplophoridae: Decapoda: Crustacea): phylogeny, taxonomy and evolution studied by a combination of morphological and molecular methods. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 186 (1), 213 - 232. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zly 039" type="journal article" year="2019">
Lunina 
<emphasis box="[1076,1125,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
provided molecular evidence to again consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[462,616,1015,1041]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Oplophoridae</taxonomicName>
as consisting of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[810,964,1015,1041]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Oplophoridae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spence Bate" authorityYear="1888" box="[1020,1215,1015,1041]" class="Malacostraca" family="Acanthephyridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Acanthephyridae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Alves-Junior, F. A. &amp; Silva, E. S. &amp; Arau, M. S. L. C. &amp; Cardoso, I. &amp; Bertrand, A. &amp; Souza-Filho, J. F." pageId="1" pageNumber="590" pagination="401 - 442" refId="ref4623" refString="Alves-Junior, F. A., Silva, E. S., Arau, M. S. L. C., Cardoso, I., Bertrand, A. &amp; Souza-Filho, J. F. (2019) Taxonomy of deep-sea shrimps of the Superfamily Oplophoroidea Dana 1852 (Decapoda: Caridea) from Southeastern Atlantic. Zootaxa, 4613 (3), 401 - 442. https: // doi. org / 10.1164 / zootaxa. 4613.3.1" type="journal article" year="2019">
Alves-Júnior 
<emphasis box="[1379,1429,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
use both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spence Bate" authorityYear="1888" box="[344,535,1051,1077]" class="Malacostraca" family="Acanthephyridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Acanthephyridae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[598,752,1051,1077]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Oplophoridae</taxonomicName>
in their paper on the taxonomy of deep-sea shrimps from Brazilian waters of the southwestern Atlantic. In light of these molecular ambiguities, I believe it to be conservative here to use, for the time being, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[500,658,1123,1149]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Oplophoridae</taxonomicName>
. as the family to which the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", G. O. Sars" authorityYear="1877" box="[1038,1184,1123,1149]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Hymenodora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1038,1184,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="590">Hymenodora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
